File: Discovery. JOHANNESBURG - Discovery Health has allocated funding for members to receive the coronavirus vaccine. Discovery Health's Chief Commercial Officer, Ronald Whelan, says the company is working closely with both government and the private sector to ensure the entire country receives these vaccinations. READ: Discovery hit by ruling over products "Discovery has allocated funding for vaccinating all members of the scheme," he said. "In fact, we got board approval a good six weeks ago on that, secondly it will be for all members of the medical scheme but I think I should mention that we will need to follow strict prioritisation criteria." For more, watch the interview with Prof Adrian Puren, HoD National Institute for Communicable Diseases above. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs